Fits polynomial curves to microtubule positions from 3D template matching
    STAR files. Runs a 4-step pipeline inside ChimeraX:
      1. Fit    - seed-and-grow curve fitting
      2. Clean  - remove duplicate/overlapping tubes
      3. Connect - join broken tube segments by trajectory extrapolation
      4. Predict - assign initial angles from template matching data
